# Solution Notes

The reference implementation treats Postgres as durable session truth and Redis as a runtime cache only.

Key fixes:

- Repeated login callbacks are keyed by `login_event_id` and return the existing app session.
- Route authorization re-checks current organization membership on every request.
- A revoked Postgres session denies access even when Redis still contains an active runtime session.
- Expired high-risk sessions write operator-readable audit reasons and details.
- Hidden evaluator tests target Redis-only sessions, stale organization context, duplicate callback replay, and audit completeness.

The intended production-path fix touches `reconciler.ts`, `middleware.ts`, and `sweeper.ts`; shallow patches that only update fixture helpers should fail the Docker-backed integration gate.
